            {
                title: "What is plantar fasciitis?",
                content: [
                    {
                        text: "Plantar fasciitis is pain from the strong band of tissue under the foot — the plantar fascia — where it attaches to the heel bone. It is one of the most common causes of heel pain. The pain is usually felt under the heel or along the arch, not at the back of the ankle (that pattern fits better with Achilles problems). For the first practical steps, see our ",
                    },
                    {
                        text: "Stage 1: Foundation guide",
                        href: "/guide/plantar-fasciitis/stage-1",
